text: Al-Shabaab or Al-Shabab (الشباب ash-Shabāb) is an Arabic phrase meaning "the Youth". It may refer to: *Al-Shabaab (militant group), a Somalia-based cell of the militant Islamist group Al-Qaeda *Al-Shabab Club (Manama), a football club in Bahrain *Al-Shabab SC (Baghdad), a football club in Iraq *Al-Shabab SC (Al Ahmadi), a football club in Kuwait *Al-Shabab SC (Seeb), a football club in Oman *Al Shabab FC (Riyadh), a football club in Saudi Arabia *Al-Shabab Dubai, a football club in the United Arab Emirates *Shabaab al Jabal, Libyan football club ==Related pages== *Ash-Shabab al-Mu'min or Houthis, a Zaidi Shia insurgent group operating in Yemen *RNOV Shabab Oman,Navy vessels of Oman *Shabaab (film), (Hindi: शबाब "Youth") 1954 Indian film *Shabab Rural District, an administrative subdivision of Iran *Shabab, Iran, a village in Iran
title: Al-Shabab
